Project Darkstar Sample Client
Version @VERSION@

INTRODUCTION

The Project Darkstar Server is a system that enables developers to write
scalable, reliable, persistent and fault-tolerant game server
applications using simple single-threaded, event-driven code.

This distribution includes the source code for developing and running
clients that communicate with each other and with game servers
implemented as applications that run in the Project Darkstar Server
environment.

CONTENTS

The SGS Software Development Kit (SDK) contains the following
subdirectories:

- src
  Source code files

- test
  Source code for tests

BUILDING

The Sun Game Server makes use of two other open source projects.

- Apache MINA, version 1.1:

  http://mina.apache.org/downloads.html

- Simple Logging Facade for Java (SLF4J), version 1.4:

  http://www.slf4j.org/download.html

KNOWN ISSUES

- The SDK only includes
 does not provide J2ME, C, or C++ implementations of the client
  API, although developers can use the documentation of the network
  protocol to develop their own implementations

 


MORE INFORMATION

For more information, please see the tutorials in the tutorial directory
and the documentation in the docs directory.  Also check the
http://www.projectdarkstar.com website, which has links to more
information and to the Project Darkstar forums.

See the CHANGELOG file for a list of changes.

If you cannot find an answer to your question in any of these places,
please email the Darkstar team at:

   ProjectDarkstar@games.dev.java.net
